r.�Welcome to the Rala Waterways, our little ��home away from home,�� if you can call it that.A little ways in is the Civic Arboretum, where we grow vegetables to help feed Adoulin.
1�In better days, good-for-nothing kids would abscond down here and engage in all manner of miscreant behavior.
1�Now, though, monsters have taken root, forcing all but the most hearty aboveground.
1�Another one of the Peacekeeperrrs' cronies, here to cause trouble in the name of ��orrrder��?
1�We've no need of your help. Surrre, some of our plantations have been shut down, but we're getting along fine.
1�I suppose I can grant you entrance into the Civic Arboretum.
1�I wouldn't go much farther, though. Things have gotten quite hairy with all the monsters popping up of late.
1�I'll let you in on a little secretaru!The Peacekeepers' Coalition puts on a brave front, but even they don't know where the monsters-wonsters came from!
1�I betaru that they were able to get in because the buildings around here are old and decrepit. A perfectaru breeding ground, if you will.
1�These vegetables don't satiate my hungerrr...what I really want are some good fish!
1�Lucky for me there are some good fishing spots right around the Arrrboretum.
1�We put all our effortaru into cultivating these vegetables, but they pale in comparison to what we could grow aboveground.
1�If the pioneering efforts are successful, we will likely no longer have to use such unnatural methods.
1�We put all our effortaru into cultivating these vegetables, but they pale in comparison to what we could grow aboveground.
1�Who am I? Oh, I representaru the Civic Arboretum Workers' Union. Pleased to make your acquaintance.
1�Kyff asked you to take some seeds to Erisa? She certainly did seem a bit down. I'm sure the seeds will cheer her up.
1�Excuse me, �[sir/ma'am]? You are a pioneer, correct? Could I bother you for a few moments?
1�Do you have spare time?A few minutes is fine.Sorry, I'm too busy.
1�Thank you for your consideration. Those of us who work here are cultivating all manner of plants, but recently we ran out of 5����.
1�Unfortunately, our charges will not grow here without them.
1�The Inventors' Coalition, however, manufactures 5���� in bulk. If you have a chance to visit their headquarters, would you mind picking some up for me?
1�Thank you for taking time out of your busy day.
1�I understand. If you ever find yourself in need of work, come see me again.
1�You have brought 6���� for me? Words are not enough to express my gratitude!
1�Yes, I am aware that in ideal circumstances, we would be using proper farmland to grow our bounty, not underground here and relying on 5����.
1�But there's no land beyond Jorius Yett for those who wield spades instead of swords or spells. This is the only way we can try to meet the increased demand from the recent population explosion.
1�If the pioneering efforts are successful, we will likely no longer have to use such unnatural methods.
1�Until that day comes, we will continue to strive to provide Adoulin with the foodstuffs the populace needs to feed itself.
1�Back to your reward, however. I hope that this will suffice.
1�The Inventors' Coalition, however, manufactures 5���� in bulk. If you have a chance to visit their headquarters, would you mind picking some up for me?

1�If you really want 6���� that badly, I guess I can let you in on a little secretaru. I'd never go because even taking one step into the battlegrounds sends paralyzing shiver-wivers down my spine, but word has it that there are some trees left in Yahse Hunting Grounds.
1�Thanks for offering to deliver those tomatoes.Don't you dare drop them, though, or the ghosts of us crestfallen researchers will hauntaru you even into the afterlife!
1�I'd sure love to have a tit-for-tataru with you, but Arciela awaits in the castle!As for the tomatoes, take heart--I've already sent Fremilla ahead with them.
s?�Ygnas has already collected the day's shipment of 5����.
1�Assuming he is to deliver them to the kitchen, I'd wager he's back at the castle by now.
1�Whaddya want? Can't you see I'm busy?
1�Ohoho, look at my precious little babies, growing so big!
1�My my, you sweeties sure are looking pretty! I bet you could make Arciela jealous!
1�Oy, Mukki, you'd better not be sucking up all the nutrients, y'hear!?
1�What's wrong with you? Not enough fertilizer or somethin'?
1�<Sigh> How long am I going to have to spend in this hellhole?
1�Damned beasts destroyed my ship, and it'll take years before I can save up enough money for a new one...
1�I've even had to rope my wife into working, too. What kind of a husband does that?
1�Ever since my hubby lost his boat, the lovely Arciela has been so good to us.
1�She even helped the two of us find employment down here.
1�It's a far sight better than doing nothing! And in an odd way, I've come to think of these lovely little plants as my children.
1�The Civic Arboretum provides us with a stable food source, but finding provisions wasn't always so simple.
1�The Adoulin Islands are so tiny that space was at a premium. Only the smallest of orchards could prosper in any sort of way.
1�We imported all of our other comestibles. For example, Zulkheim flour has always been a hot commodity in these parts.
1�Of course, the arboretum isn't some agricultural panacea. We still have to rely mainly on trade with other countries for most victuals.
1�Hopefully this place will be the first step in self-sufficiency for our nation.
1�You scribbled down some information regarding 6����.
1�Why howdy-wowdy, stranger! I'm Jaroney-Baroney, geomancer in training!
1�The cyclical flow of wataru in the area helps to maintain balance not just for the vegetables we grow, but also for geomantic-wantic harmony.
1�My master sent me down here to study the flow of energy in this area, and my heartaru is aflutter with what I might learn!
1�I-I'm really in for it now! They sent me for maintenance...where all the monsters are!?
1�My superiors bestowed on me a rune of p-protection, but...even if it works on monsters, it doesn't do a thing f-for my nerves!
1�I wouldn't go past the gates if I were you...but if you're determined, make sure you're prepared for the dangers within.
1�And I don't just mean the monsters. Which gates are opening depends on the day and time, so if you aren't careful, you may find yourself in trouble should you need to beat a hasty retreat!
1�Please forgive us for the raptor incident.
1�That being said, shouldn't you be heading back to the Mummers' Coalition to let them know the raptors are safe and unharmed?
1�This is the Watergarden Coliseum, where the Mummers' Coalition holds periodic rrraptor fights.
1�No raptor fights are currrently scheduled. You'll have to come back at a later date to satisfy your bloodlust.
1�This is the Watergarden Coliseum, where the Mummers' Coalition holds periodic rrraptor fights.
1�No raptor fights are currrently scheduled. You'll have to come back at a later date to satisfy your bloodlust.
1�This place is one where only a select few may engage in sacrrred battles.
1�Oh, you're here on behalf of the Peacekeeperrrs' Coalition?
1�That must have been quite the crrrawl.
1�As you experienced for yourself, the labyrrrinthine corridors are quite confounding, and have stymied many before you.
1�But making the jourrrney once makes subsequent visits all the easier, wouldn't you agree?
1�Along the way you must have come acrrross another gate with a symbol etched in stone.
1�Predictably, this gate is not like the otherrrs.
1�Passage is grrranted to specific individuals, and no one else.
1�These stories are best left for another time. I'm sure those who ordered you to confirrrm the status of the gates are waiting for word.
1�Me? There is no need for self-intrrroductions, as you've certainly heard my name before.
1�While you're at it, the Peacekeepers will be grrrateful for any assistance you can provide in keeping the road back safe for travel.
1�They must be waiting for you in the city prrroper. Hurry now.
1�What awe-inspiring rrrunic energy...Where have you been all this time!? We've been eagerrrly awaiting your arrival.
1�Prrreparations for the event are complete. When you're ready, just claw your way to the door at your rrrear.
1�You're after the Dashing Drrreamers?
1�Funny, that. They waltzed into the coliseum clutching a couple of barrrels from the warehouse nearby.
1� The Dashing Dreamers? Funny about that. The duo hauled a pairrr of squeaking barrels out the front door not two minutes ago.
1�Something about a carrrgo vessel and just desserts... I don't get paid enough to pay much attention.
1�What on Vana'diel is going on in there? Firrrst Adoulin's famous duo sneaks in through the back, and now a Tarutaru hauls tail out of here drrragging another by his coattails?
1�He flailed about like a madman, screeching something about Svenja and the Orrrder of Janniston.
1�What would one of your ilk-wilk want down here? Only authorized workers are allowed beyond this point.
1�I wouldn't expectaru a philistine of the construction arts to notice, but a veteran like me can detect even the slightest change in the water. The recent shaking definitely caused a stir.
1�One of my colleagues reportarued hearing a loud crack, like a bomb going off.Hmm...6Yes, I imagine that would put us in a bit of a pickle-wickle.
1�It's all we can do to even find the source. Repairing it? Bah, you'd better hope those pioneers're good for more than just traipsing-waipsing in the jungle!
1�The waterways're vital to all who live in Adoulin, so don't be thinkin' 'bout causin' no trouble!
1�So I was just here, mindin' my own business, see? Then all of a sudden, a huge flash of light, and boom! I darn near soiled m'self!
1�Th' area's gone a bit foul, and I'm 'fraid it'll take a while 'fore things're back to normal.
1�But boy, take a gander at this! It's part of a wooden fuse, wouldn't ya say? How crazy would ya hafta be to try to blow up the waterways!?
1�You stand at the Peacekeepers' Coalition's outpost in Rala Waterways. I, Relentless Storm, am in charge of our operations in the area.
1�This must be the area the Couriers' Coalition mentioned.You leave the package in the designated location.
1�Yet something is amiss. You can't quite put your finger on it, but you feel like someone is gazing at you from afar. Report back to Vaulois before things get out of hand.
1�This murky haze...what could it mean?
1�Can't you feel the deeply oppressive air bearing down on your shoulders? It must be the darkness of the jungle made manifest.
1�Is it just me? Am I the only one who notices this ominous haze?
1�Still, it couldn't hurt to make a protective charm to ward off evil.

1�According to the rituals taught to me by a local geomancer, I need 
 %����.
1�But I can't do it alone. Please, will you lend me your aid?
1�Assist him in gathering materials?Certainly.Sounds too dangerous...

1�You have my gratitude. The only way to resist the primordial darkness is with this kind of protection. Remember what I need--
 %����.
1�I suppose I cannot fault you. Yet the darkness is approaching...something must be done before it envelops us all.

1�My mother has fallen ill from worry. Could this be related to...? I must create more charms. Please, bring me 
 %����.
1�Trade them to me once you have the appropriate number.
